A4.text: Mansfield Park is the third published novel by the English author Jane Austen, first published in 1814 by Thomas Egerton.

A5.text: The novel tells the story of Fanny Price, starting when her overburdened family sends her at the age of ten to live in the household of her wealthy aunt and uncle and following her development into early adulthood.
